Imperative:
It will have a set of condition to proceed with single line execution to run or create the objects.

Declarative:
Directly reach the destination with the yaml file to run or create a object.
Local file > live object configuration file > json - last applied configuration

Whenever we use apply command to change or remove or add fields in the local file, it will be applied to live object configuration 
and updated to last applied configuration.

Imperative commands:
kubectl run nginx --image=nginx
kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx
kubectl expose pod nginx --name=svc-nginx --port=80
kubectl expose deployment nginx --port=80
kubectl edit deployment nginx
kubectl scale deployment nginx --replicas=3
kubectl set image deployment nginx nginx=nginx:1.18


Declarative commands:
kubectl apply -f deployment.yml
